<TEXT>
four democratic state legislators 
announced monday that they were switching to the republican party 
earning them praise from president bush 
state reps frank ely alvin endt danny guice and curtis 
holston jr told reporters they had considered the change for about 
a year 
im not leaving the democrats they left me long ago endt 
said 
my thoughts are conservative and being associated with the 
republican party is being associated with the more conservative 
political party he said 
the four were accompanied at news conferences in pascagoula and 
jackson by ron farris of the state gop farris read a letter from 
bush who lauded the lawmakers for their tremendous courage in 
switching allegiances 
ely said he feels more like a republican than a democrat 
my philosophy is more along the lines of the republican party 
i feel that the democrats left me he said 
the four are up for reelection in november 1991 and said they 
decided to go public with their switch in plenty of time for 
constituents to make up their minds 
since november 1988 more than 65 elected democrats in 
mississippi have switched to the gop 
ely who was elected to the legislature in 1984 said many of 
his constituents had called to tell him they were happy about his 
decision to switch i havent had the first negative response 
he said 
guice said he decided to become a republican because he felt 
state and national democratic leaders are too liberal 
i realized that ive been supporting republicans for some time 
now said guice who was elected to the mississippi house in 1983 
guice said the gop did not court the four 
holston who was elected in 1983 said he identifies more with 
the republican party he said he doesnt expect resistance from the 
people who voted him into office 
i think the majority will be pleased to see that im joining 
the republican party holston said the feeling of my area has 
changed toward republicans since i was originally elected as a 
democrat 
</TEXT>
