<TEXT>
edward h moreno a newsman in the santa 
fe bureau of the associated press has been named correspondent in 
charge of the bureau 
the appointment was announced monday by albuquerque chief of 
bureau mark mittelstadt moreno succeeds jw bill feather who 
is retiring after 32 years with the ap 
moreno 36 joined the ap in santa fe in 1983 after working for 
newspapers in three states he is a native of mexico city and a 
graduate of the university of northern colorado 
moreno began his journalism career on a colorado weekly and 
later worked for the scottsbluff neb star herald and the new 
mexican of santa fe 
