<TEXT>
picture the nations greatest natural 
treasures the grand canyon yellowstone national park olympic 
national forest gary ind 
gary ind 
an alaska congressman who resents an indiana colleagues 
involvement in debate over the pacific northwests timber supply 
wants to recreate the ancient forests over 13 million acres of 
northwest indiana 
the tongueincheek plan to establish a new national forest in 
indiana was circulated among lawmakers in response to rep jim 
jontzs call to protect oldgrowth forests in california oregon 
and washington 
this is a novel approach in that it would seek to recreate 
ancient forests of the region which have been decimated by 
