does the nation need a penetrating bomber to attack mobile 
targets in the soviet union when the warsaw pact has collapsed as a 
military alliance and the kremlin is faced with economic woes and 
ethnic unrest 
as the federal deficit increases can the country afford the 
most expensive aircraft in history when some suggest b1 bombers 
and b52s equipped with cruise missiles will suffice until 2030 
will the government spend nearly 10 billion on a single program 
in the mid1990s 
faced with the public calls for cuts in defense the parochial 
military demands in an election year and the changing strategy 
many lawmakers find killing the b2 an easy answer 
the decision wont be made for several months but for now the 
issue provides an opportunity for opponents to provide the rhetoric 
the stealth is a budgetary black hole it attracts and 
devours public funds like a condensed star attracts and devours 
light said sen joseph lieberman dconn 
</TEXT>
