<TEXT>
here is a chronology of 18yearold ryan whites battle with 
aids and his struggle to attend school 
december 1984 white 13 is diagnosed as having contracted 
aids through a bloodclotting agent used to treat his hemophilia 
july 30 1985 western schools corp superintendent james o 
smith bars white from school near kokomo ind saying the health 
risk for other children is too great 
aug 3 the state board of health sets guidelines for admitting 
children with aids to school saying white should attend class as 
long as hes not severely ill 
aug 8 whites family sues in federal court to get him 
admitted to school a judge says administrative appeals must be 
exhausted first 
aug 26 classes begin at western middle school ryan is linked 
to school by a computertelephone hookup 
nov 25 indiana department of education hearing officer rules 
white should be allowed to go to school when he is not intensely 
sick 
feb 6 1986 an appeals board rules white now 14 can attend 
classes with clearance from the howard county health officer 
clearance is granted 
feb 19 a howard county judge rejects request by parents and 
students to bar white from school 
feb 21 white attends a halfday of school a howard county 
judge later in the day approves a temporary injunction preventing 
him from attending school 
april 10 a clinton county circuit judge lifts the injunction 
white returns to class later that day 
summer 1987 whites family moves to cicero about 20 miles 
away saying they didnt want to stay where they were unwanted 
aug 31 white attends his first day of classes as a freshman 
at hamilton heights high school no protests are reported 
march 3 1988 ryan testifies before the white house aids 
commission saying i came face to face with death at 13 years 
old but decided to live a normal life 
aug 18 filming begins in north carolina of the ryan white 
story an abc television movie it is broadcast on jan 16 1989 
dec 16 1989 white turns 18 in ill health 
march 29 1990 white is admitted to riley childrens hospital 
in indianapolis suffering from a respiratory infection 
april 2 the announcement is made that white is in critical 
condition on a lifesupport system 
april 8 white dies 
</TEXT>
