agreement today to trade pepsicola for ships and vodka 
the deal is the largest between a us corporation and the 
soviet union and comes just two months before a ummit between 
president bush and soviet leader mikhail s gorbachev 
it represents more than 3 billion in retail sales of pepsicola 
and stolichnaya russian vodka and would make pepsicola more widely 
available in the soviet union 
since 1974 the purchase nybased company has shipped its 
softdrink syrup to the soviet union where it is made into cola 
and sold in bottles the company took its profits out in vodka 
