soviet jewish immigrants 
celebrated their first passover in this jewish settlement monday 
marking their ancestors release from slavery in ancient egypt and 
the modern exodus from the soviet union 
i see similarities between the passover story and the russian 
immigration said suzanna eisenvarg 38 she was among 130 new 
immigrants who joined with settlers for a passover meal in the 
elementary school gymnasium 
its delicious ms eisenvarg said as she tried the 
chorosot a pate of apple nuts and wine which represents the 
mortar that the jews used to build pyramids for egyptian pharaohs 
she recalled that in leningrad we brought matzo from the 
synagogue we would just eat matzo on that night somehow we knew 
the date the date that israelites left egypt she said 
as she spoke rabbi boris yussin a russian immigrant who lives 
in jerusalem translated the hebrew story into russian while 
israelis took turns reading from the hagada which tells the story 
of the jews flight from egypt 
mrs eisenvarg is one of about 250 soviet jews living in the 
occupied west bank a little less than 1 percent of the 29000 
immigrants who arrived in 1989 and the first three months of 1990 
the pace is apparently quickening soviet jewish immigration 
activist natan sharansky estimated the total for this year at 
200000 
the presence of soviet jews in the occupied lands has 
complicated the exodus by sparking criticism from the united states 
and galvanizing an arab campaign against all soviet immigration 
mrs eisenvarg and other new arrivals said they settled in ariel 
because unlike israel apartments were plentiful and cheap none 
cited ideological reasons for being in ariel a settlement of about 
8000 people in the heart of the west bank 
ariels mayor ron nachman said the recent arrivals had been 
calling relatives in moscow and leningrad urging them to come and 
settle in ariel 
he said that with the us policy against settlements in the 
occupied lands we have to push as much as possible for them to 
come here 
he said israel will weather the protests over the settlement of 
jews in the warwon land 
there was a pharaoh in egypt and we got through that and we 
will get through this too this immigration is a miracle he said 
reuven rosenthal 34 came to ariel eight months ago with his 
wife and two children its a nice pretty place with good cheap 
prices said rosenthal 
he said he was not concerned about the frequent clashes between 
jewish settlers and palestinian activists at his doorstep what 
should i be afraid of in the soviet union there is much more fear 
of antisemitism he said 
the gymnasium was decorated with yellow blue and purple 
streamers passover ingredients such as eggs apples wine nutmeg 
and horseradish covered the yellow clothcovered round tables 
for most soviet jews who have been cut off from jewish 
traditions all their lives this marked the first time they 
participated in a seder or passover dinner 
passover is one of the most important holidays in the jewish 
calendar 
during the meal held on the first evening of the holiday jews 
eat food symbolizing the passover themes of redemption and freedom 
and read the story of the exodus from egypt one key ingredient is 
matzo or unleavened bread symbolizing the haste with which the 
jews had to leave egypt 
while the soviet immigrants in ariel celebrated their 
homecoming their presence in the west bank continues to strain 
relations between israel and the rest of the world 
us officials say settling immigrants in the occupied lands and 
israeliannexed arab east jerusalem raises obstacles to peace last 
month secretary of state james a baker iii suggested washington 
withhold special financial aid for immigrant absorption until 
israel pledged not to settle soviet jews in the occupied lands 
arab and plo leaders fear that the expected arrival of about 
750000 soviet jews in this decade will cause more suffering to the 
palestinians they claim that palestinians will eventually be 
ousted from the west bank and gaza strip to make room for new 
arrivals from the soviet union 
in response to the arab campaign the soviet union has refused 
to ratify an agreement with israel for direct moscowtel aviv 
flights that would expedite jewish emigration soviet jews now 
arrive in israel via eastern european transit points there are 
long waits for a limited number of seats 
</TEXT>
