interest rates on shortterm treasury 
securities fell in mondays auction to their lowest level in a 
month 
the treasury department sold 82 billion in threemonth bills 
at an average discount rate of 780 percent down from 783 percent 
last week another 82 billion was sold in sixmonth bills at the 
same average discount rate of 780 percent down from 781 percent 
last week 
the rates were the lowest since threemonth bills sold for 772 
percent on feb 26 and sixmonth bills averaged 779 percent on 
march 5 
the new discount rates understate the actual return to investors 
807 percent for threemonth bills with a 10000 bill selling 
for 980280 and 823 percent for a sixmonth bill selling for 
960570 
in a separate report the federal reserve said monday that the 
average yield for oneyear treasury bills the most popular index 
for making changes in adjustable rate mortgages fell to 829 
percent last week down from 834 percent the previous week 
