the fort myers fla newspress won the 
robert f kennedy journalism awards 2000 grand prize monday for 
far from the dream a 12part series on the problems of blacks 
in southwestern florida 
the newspress which also received a 1000 first prize for 
print journalism was honored for its articles last year on 
housing education economics politics and other problems 
affecting poor blacks 
the awards committee said that as a result of the series the 
lee county fla school board took steps to hire more minority 
teachers the county director of public housing was suspended and 
the justice department and the naacp legal defense fund requested a 
study of the countys desegregation policy of busing only black 
children 
the newspress will receive its awards at a may 14 reception at 
the suburban virginia home of ethel kennedy widow of the former 
new york senator who was assassinated during his 1968 presidential 
campaign the awards sponsored by the robert f kennedy memorial 
are given for outstanding coverage of the problems of disadvantaged 
americans 
the firstprize winner in television was a team from wgbh the 
boston public tv station for the aids quarterly with peter 
jennings winter 1989 
national public radio won a first prize for young black men 
lost generation and stormi greener of the minneapolis star and 
tribune was awarded first prize in the photojournalism category 
