the area was quickly sealed off and police and soldiers were 
airlifted in to search for clues 
police said the blast created a crater 15 feet deep and 40 feet 
wide and hurled the vehicle into a nearby field crushed like a 
sardine tin 
several other soldiers traveling in front in another land rover 
suffered shock said a spokesman for the royal ulster constabulary 
the soldiers were members of the ulster defense regiment the 
mainly protestant locally recruited regiment of the british army 
said the spokesman speaking anonymously in keeping with british 
custom 
a pair of overalls was found a halfmile from the site of the 
explosion security chiefs then warned all police and army units 
that an attack might be imminent 
on friday the irish supreme court ruled not to extradite owen 
carron a former northern ireland member of parliament saying he 
was a political prisoner 
you take these murders of these four people today alongside 
those decisions in the supreme court of the republic not to 
extradite those accused of violent crime and one is very very 
depressed mrs thatcher said 
violent crime is not political its common criminal she 
said 
the court had issued a similar ruling earlier three weeks 
earlier in which it refused to extradite escaped prisoners saying 
they would be subject to assault by prison guards if they were 
returned 
the irish republican army is fighting to end british rule in 
northern ireland and unite the predominantly protestant province 
with the roman catholic republic of ireland 
</TEXT>
