<TEXT>
an early morning blaze on board the 
irish sea car ferry norrona killed one man and injured 32 people on 
monday police said and both police and the ships owner said 
arson was suspected 
the ferry was carrying 297 people from milford haven 180 miles 
west of london to rosslare ireland and was eight miles off wales 
when the fire was discovered the blaze damaged 10 cabins 
the b and i shipping line with headquarters in dublin ireland 
issued a statement saying it suspected the norrona fire was started 
deliberately the company said the blaze began in two of norronas 
unoccupied sleeping cabins 
it did not elaborate but the companys marine superintendent 
