the latest news a 24page tabloid billed as 
the nations first hourly newspaper made its debut april 2 on a 
midafternoon flight from washington to new york 
the paper will be available on pan am shuttles originating at 
national airport from 330 to 630 pm on the theory that 
corporate passengers have been starved all day for news 
the paper is updated hourly with copy from united press 
international and states news service to provide breaking news 
business developments and weather reports advertising is sold by 
financial world magazine 
the partners plan to expand distribution to boston and new york 
after a test period they also are considering heavily traveled air 
routes between los angeles and san francisco chicago and st 
louis and houston and dallas 
a radio station in print is how editor and publisher leland 
schwartz described the venture in a frontpage letter to readers in 
the first edition of the first issue 
there are critics who think were crazy schwartz admitted 
in the article but he noted that the same people returning to new 
york were so hungry when you came down to washington this 
morning the shuttle was a sea of newspapers 
the maiden 330 pm edition contained frontpage articles on 
the new york and tokyo stock markets and a list of headlines to 
stories on inside pages featured inside were news briefs sports 
briefs 1 pm stock data and the latest filings with the 
securities and exchange commission as well as short stories on the 
top news of the day 
