i think this is one of the most thorough evaluations of small 
newspapers ever undertaken said jim herman editor of the 
traverse city recordeagle in michigan and chairman of the 
societys project on excellence in small newspapers 
our goal is to find small newspapers that are doing 
outstanding jobs and to learn from them 
herman said asnes selection process began last fall when 1356 
small daily newspapers were invited to compete more than 450 
newspapers were submitted for consideration and regional judges 
narrowed that field to 74 finalists 
in january 13 judges gathered at the poynter institute in st 
petersburg fla and selected the 10 winners the judges included 
editors journalism teachers and readers 
the papers were graded on a wide range of criteria herman 
said one of the most important was that they have an independent 
style and that they have a strong sense of place 
it was the second year asne has honored excellent small 
