<TEXT>
no one in the ronald reagan administration 
with the possible exception of secretary of state george shultz 
achieved the stature that jim baker did 
as white house chief of staff he cultivated members of congress 
from the start and rolled up legislative victories that eluded 
other couriers of the reagan program he also assiduously courted 
the news media provoking donald regan his successor as chief of 
staff to tell a republican group that he was appalled at the 
amount of time baker spent with reporters and thencia director 
william casey to complain that baker was the biggest leaker in town 
but his supporters credited baker with pushing the essential 
elements of reagans firstterm agenda through congress including 
those surprisingly early triumphs on the budget and taxes 
fashioned by luring boll weevil democrats into a new hill 
majority 
some critics fault him for just those successes saying he too 
often orchestrated shortterm victories without much caring about 
the lasting consequences a burgeoning federal deficit foremost 
among them 
he was much more of a mr fixit than planner much more 
interested in politics than in policy said former reagan 
treasury official john e chapoton a onetime law partner and 
neighbor of bakers 
william a niskanen jr a former member of the council of 
economic advisers said he doesnt bring any particular 
convictions to bear on a job other than doing a good job i 
dont think he has any particular vision 
david stockman director of the office of management and budget 
during bakers tenure at the white house wrote that baker was 
deep down neither very versed on matters of policy nor intensely 
interested in them 
baker at the time admitted as much i dont consider myself 
as one who has deeply held views on specific issues he told 
washingtonian magazine in 1982 
baker might have found himself the odd man out among reagans 
coterie of californians around the oval office but under a plan 
drawn up by his prickly but creative sidekick richard g darman 
he quickly managed to seize control of the white house paper flow 
to the president 
with that came power particularly the ability to knife his 
enemies and praise his own work according to an undelighted but 
impressed paul m weyrich president of the superconservative free 
congress research and education foundation 
