walking alone on the sidewalk 
he was someone many of you would have recognized a chief of 
staff in a previous administration baker said there he was 
alone no reporters no security no adoring public no trappings 
of power just one solitary man alone with his thoughts 
that mental picture continually serves to remind me of the 
impermanence of power and place that man had it all but only for 
a time that memory puts my own life in perspective 
