<TEXT>
hes a composer for our time a man who writes 
operas about the social condition of the modern world sir michael 
tippett though better known in his native england than in america 
has been called one of the three or four giant composers in the 
last half of the 20th century 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
sir michael tippett the 85yearold british 
composer who was briefly jailed as a pacifist during world war ii 
is a musician with a message 
to him the sight of young people dancing on the berlin wall was 
a marvelous piece of theater for one thing no shots were 
fired 
for 50 years sir michael has been writing his philosophical 
reflections on world events into his oratorio and opera libretti 
ever since ts eliot gave him some tips for writing a child of 
our time which became his first major success 
a child of our time was inspired by a young jew who killed a 
nazi official in paris providing the excuse for kristallnacht the 
prelude to the holocaust 
when i wrote a child of our time i had to come out from any 
notion that what i was writing was just for my countrymen says 
the silverhaired composer i had to write something about a 
condition that seemed to me really universal 
sir michaels opera king priam used a greek myth to explore 
politics power and choice his opera the ice break explores 
violence racism and political turmoil 
in the knot garden one of his characters was a scarred 
woman he thought of her as a french underground fighter whod been 
tortured by the gestapo in world war ii when the opera was 
performed recently in melbourne australia the character became a 
chinese student in tiananmen square 
sir michael who attended the performance approved of the 
change 
if a work has value it will proceed in this way from a now to 
another now he says 
