25 years conducting his big orchestral works 
in operas he puts together these fantastical collages of 
allegory i think his philosophical approach to the problems of 
complicated urbanized society has won him a great deal of friends 
among young people and people that share his concerns 
when he was about 25 sir michael was strongly impressed by the 
movie the four horsemen of the apocalypse starring rudolph 
valentino in which a father wanders among the white crosses of a 
cemetery in flanders 
i realized all those wonderful young people had gone to the 
ground and never had a life at all he says when it came to 
the next war it came to me that these young people could have been 
scapegoats people thrown out by a society i had to sing in some 
way about them i could not get them out of my mind theyre there 
to this day 
in england where he is better known than he is in america sir 
michael has a fan club and members get just as paul mccartneys 
fans do a newsletter about his activities performances and 
recordings 
the kent opera is currently taking king priam on tour to six 
cities 
sir michael is conducting one recording a year of his 
compositions for nimbus records his eyesight is failing making it 
difficult for him to conduct concerts recordings are easier 
when covent garden was rehearsing sir michaels the ice 
break in 1977 he told a reporter hed never write another opera 
that answer was given at the time i knew i was getting on in 
age and strength he says i had already decided i would like 
to do a big work for voices and orchestra for the concert hall it 
became the mask of time 
after having completed the mask of time i still was very 
vigorous and the theater took over again i dont quite know why it 
did but it did 
sir michael celebrated becoming 85 on jan 2 by accepting 
invitations to hear his music played in several cities 
the university of cincinnatis collegeconservatory of music 
performed his opera the knot garden sir michael called the 
performances brilliant and the production masterly adding and 
ive seen a lot of them 
the cincinnati symphony performed his lyrical fantasia 
concertante on a theme of corelli 
at intermission a young woman was overheard to say i liked 
the mozart but the tippett completely blew me away i loved it 
jesus lopezcobos music director of the cincinnati symphony 
says i think tippett is one of the big composers of british 
composers benjamin britten is more known here i think tippetts 
time will come too 
about britten sir michael says we were mildly rivals if you 
like we both wanted to go into theater we didnt think the operas 
of the preceding generation were workable 
sir michael says that on the eve of his entering prison for 
three months in world war ii as a pacifist britten was much more 
frightened than i was 
now he says the world is changing very quickly to my great 
delight and surprise ive lived long enough to see young people 
dancing on the berlin wall a marvelous piece of theater for one 
who believes you cant really do it by guns it was done in another 
way 
