those are the kinds of questions people regularly ask williams 
president of the joint center for political studies a littleknown 
research institute he has built into the countrys premier black 
think tank 
the center has a staff of 60 providing research on the social 
political and economic activities and concerns of africanamericans 
it is most well known for the annual roster of black elected 
officials which has charted the growth of black officeholders 
from the 600 it originally listed to the more than 7000 now 
included 
the center now occupies a special political niche at a time when 
black candidates and voters are playing an increasingly influential 
role in national and local politics 
the mainstream is the new frontier for black politicians 
williams says citing the 1989 elections of wilder in virginia and 
david dinkins as mayor of new york 
thats where the jobs are he says all of the positions 
that are in predominantly black jurisdictions have just about been 
filled 
largely disenfranchised in many southern states until the 
