<TEXT>
it may seem odd for kevin kline to play a 
philandering pizza parlor owner in the outrageous new film i love 
you to death and then star in and direct hamlet offbroadway 
but the versatile goodlooking actor shuttles from bigbudget 
movie to shakespeare classic with ease its something he has done 
for the last decade or so alternating bigleague bard like 
richard iii henry v and much ado about nothing with 
films like sophies choice silverado and a fish called 
wanda 
i love you to death is black comedy opera buffo without 
the music its a flamboyant motion picture filled with purple 
passion and bananapeel humor as a mousy wife tracey ullman 
tries again and again to murder her adulterous husband kline 
not exactly the melancholy dane which is klines other current 
project and now on view at the new york shakespeare festival 
public theater its a role he first did there four years ago and 
his return to it is a rarity american actors usually dont get a 
second chance with hamlet 
in england there is a tradition of doing hamlet twice and 
i can understand why the genial softspoken kline was saying 
the other day like any great classical part you can only get 
part of it when you do it once there are so many different ways to 
go its the biggest open door in theater 
klines initial attempt at hamlet in 1986 was thoughtful 
clearspoken and introspective but the production directed by 
liviu ciulei received mixed reviews 
there were rumors that i was unhappy with my first hamlet 
he says of course i was unhappy with it ill be unhappy 
with this one there is no way to be completely satisfied with any 
given production of hamlet and theres also no way to satisfy a 
large group of people its like a rorschach test everybody has 
their very own personal response to the play 
while preparing for that first hamlet kline knew he would 
do it a second time it was something he and joseph papp head of 
the shakespeare festival knew they would do going into it i 
said i dont want to do this just once kline recalls and 
papp agreed 
what he hadnt planned on was directing the play himself his 
first job at directing steven berkoff who did a striking modern 
dress coriolanus at the public theater was to have directed 
the new production but the success of his version of oscar wildes 
salome in london kept him in england 
with papps blessing kline took over 
it was a decision that was arrived at spontaneously after 
years and years of thinking about it kline jokes i had been 
thinking about directing for a couple of years and suggested it to 
joe i thought why not direct a play i know pretty well theres 
no way you can know a play better than having played so central a 
character 
for the first time in his career kline became involved in an 
entire production not only the direction but the design sets 
costumes and lighting and casting 
was it odd sitting on the other side of the fence auditioning 
his fellow performers 
i love actors and i have a great sympathy for the audition 
process which is one of the more barbaric aspects of show 
business kline says im not a good auditioner myself so i 
take each audition with a grain of salt you cant show everything 
in an audition 
he knew the work of some of the actors like brian murray who 
plays claudius and dana ivey who plays gertrude so well that he 
didnt ask them to audition others he did sometimes even getting 
up on stage to act out scenes with them 
a lot of them said if it doesnt happen it was fun working 
on it kline says they knew that they couldnt all be in it 
the director simply has to find the actor who is best suited for 
each role 
ask kline about his ideas for hamlet and he hesitates 
begging off answering since he had just started rehearsals but 
its not one of those weird productions that set the play in mexico 
in the 19th century or some other exotic place and time he reveals 
its a nonconcept concept production he laughs right 
now it takes place where it did in shakespeares time on a stage 
that is denmark but shakespeares denmark we are just taking our 
cues from the play 
and thats how h houston ap the number of w and natural gas 
rigs declined ount showed a modest decrease after posting a gain of 
53 rigs the previous week a year ago the count was 778 baker 
hughes said monday 
baker hughes rig count the widely watched industry index of 
drilling activity reflects the number of rotary rigs actively 
exploring for oil and gas as of last friday not the number of 
producing wells 
houstonbased hughes tool co an oil toolmaker company that 
merged with baker international corp of orange calif has kept 
track of the rig count since 1940 
in december 1981 at the height of the oil boom the rig count 
reached a peak of 4500 but oil prices plunged to less than 10 
per 42gallon barrel in the summer of 1986 prompting a collapse in 
the rig count that bottomed out at 663 the lowest since hughes 
began compiling figures 
among major oilproducing states texas and colorado lost nine 
rigs each ohio was down by three and north dakota was down two 
new mexicos count increased by three rigs and the counts in 
california and louisiana each increased by one 
