along with the data base salomon is obtaining computer software 
that will give its sales trading and research staff access to 
descriptions of securities in the data base histories of their 
trading prices research and other information 
theres considerable value in all of that said mark field 
head of highyield sales at salomon this puts us in the center 
of the securities holders 
the highyield system also includes management reporting back 
office and recordkeeping features salomon said 
the purchase price wasnt disclosed but drexel said salomons 
bid was the highest from among 15 firms that had expressed interest 
in the assets 
the purchase of this system along with the recent addition of 
several experienced highyield professionals merely serves to 
underscore our continued longterm commitment to the highyield 
market c daniel tyree head of salomons highyield department 
said in a statement 
salomon has hired about five drexel junk bond specialists since 
the start of the year including the firms former head of 
highyield research joseph c bencivenga who joined salomon about 
a week ago field said 
drexel was the biggest underwriter and market maker of junk 
bonds and fostered the explosive growth of junk in the 1980s into a 
225 billion market 
the firm is liquidating as a result of the chapter 11 bankruptcy 
filing by its parent in february 
drexel has whittled its securities portfolio down from about 47 
billion to a little under 1 billion mostly junk bonds private 
placements of highyield debt and equity stakes in companies the 
firm helped finance said steven anreder a drexel spokesman 
the firm is trying to sell its portfolio in an orderly fashion 
to obtain the best prices and doesnt have a target date for 
finishing the job anreder said 
wed like to do it as expeditiously as possible but were not 
going to give it away either he said 
there are 700 to 800 people still working at drexel and that 
number should be cut in half within the next month or two anreder 
said the firm employed 5380 workers before its bankruptcy filing 
</TEXT>
