<TEXT>
the committee representing eastern airlines 
preferred shareholders proposed a reorganization plan for the 
carrier monday that would give eastern to its shareholders other 
creditors and new managers 
the move marks the first time one of the parties in easterns 
bankruptcy proceeding has challenged the airlines reorganization 
plan by submitting its own proposal 
miamibased eastern has submitted several restructuring plans 
since its chapter 11 bankruptcy filing on march 9 1989 its 
exclusive right to file a plan with the us bankruptcy court 
expired feb 20 after the court extended it several times 
eastern spokeswoman karen ceremsak in miami said the airline 
hadnt yet seen the shareholders proposal and declined comment so 
did joel zweibel an attorney for easterns unsecured creditors 
the other major group that is owed money 
the preferred shareholders committee said it filed with the 
court a plan to reorganize eastern as an independent 
standalone airline that would be owned by shareholders and 
unsecured creditors and operated by a new management team 
the shareholders committee had objected previously to easterns 
plan that would have paid them only 10 cents on the dollar 
the preferred holders whom eastern owes about 680 million 
would own 45 percent of the new airline under the plan the 
unsecured creditors who are owed 980 million would get 50 
percent of eastern the remaining 5 percent would be held by the 
new management team 
robert miller an attorney for the preferred shareholders said 
the committee has spoken to several people as possible new 
managers of eastern but he refused to identify them 
easterns unions which struck the airline on march 4 1989 
long have advocated that frank lorenzo chairman of easterns 
parent texas air corp be replaced in running eastern by a special 
courtappointed trustee the unsecured creditors unhappy with 
easterns proposals to repay them only partially indicated last 
week they also would seek a trustee 
under the preferred holders plan the unsecured creditors also 
would receive 200 million in new collateralized eastern bonds and 
50 million in cash they would get another 70 million in notes to 
be repaid from funds eastern might win in litigation against its 
parent texas air and its sister continental airlines over eastern 
assets transferred to them before the strike and bankruptcy 
the unsecured creditors include such aircraft manufacturers as 
boeing co and airbus industrie and jet engine makers like general 
electric co 
courtappointed bankruptcy examiner david i shapiro recently 
found that texas air owes eastern between 280 million and 400 
million for the difference between what it paid for the assets and 
what they were worth houstonbased texas air has offered to settle 
the potential claims by paying eastern around 280 million but the 
unions have said that is insufficient and a trustee should be 
appointed 
if the 70 million in notes were repaid the rest of the money 
from the litigation would be invested in the new airlines 
operations miller said 
he said the preferred holders have discussed their new plan with 
representatives of goldman sachs amp co financial advisers to the 
unsecured creditors 
we would hope that the unsecured creditors would be 
supportive of a reorganization rather than a liquidation miller 
said in a telephone interview we dont want to see this airline 
liquidated 
last tuesday the committee of unsecured creditors voted 
unanimously to reject easterns latest reorganization proposal 
which would give them only 25 cents for each dollar owed a 
majority of the creditors also voted to seek the appointment of a 
special trustee 
however the unsecured creditors dropped an earlier threat to 
press for a liquidation of eastern because they were concerned 
about the potentially negative impact of such a request on 
passenger bookings 
 
