bat industries plc 
bat owns farmers group inc and bidder sir james goldsmith had 
proposed to sell farmers to axamidi assurances of france upon 
acquiring bat britains biggest conglomerate 
california regulators ruled that policyholders interests would 
not be served either by a takeover of bat by goldsmiths hoylake 
investments ltd or the sale of farmers to the french company a 
key objection was that axamidi was putting no cash behind its 45 
billion offer 
